# LiVEiT® Incorrect Logo Usage

The LiVEiT® logo is a registered trademark and should always be presented consistently.

Incorrect use weakens brand recognition, reduces professionalism and may create confusion regarding official LiVEiT® products and services.

This document provides examples of modifications that are not permitted.

---

# General Principle

Only official logo artwork supplied by the LiVEiT® project should be used.

The logo should always retain its original appearance, proportions and colours.

If an appropriate version of the logo is not available, request an official asset rather than modifying an existing one.

---

# Do Not Stretch

Never stretch the logo horizontally or vertically.

Changing the proportions distorts the visual identity and reduces recognition.

---

# Do Not Compress

Do not squash or compress the logo to fit a particular layout.

Always scale the logo proportionally.

---

# Do Not Rotate

The logo should always appear in its intended orientation.

Do not rotate, tilt or invert the artwork.

---

# Do Not Recolour

Only official brand colours may be used.

Do not:

* Change colours
* Replace colours
* Apply gradients
* Add colour effects
* Create alternative colour versions

Use only the approved logo variations provided by the project.

---

# Do Not Add Effects

Do not apply visual effects such as:

* Shadows
* Outer glows
* Inner glows
* Bevels
* Embossing
* Reflections
* Filters

The official artwork already represents the intended appearance of the brand.

---

# Do Not Outline

Do not add strokes or outlines around the logo.

Additional borders alter the official design and should not be used.

---

# Do Not Crop

The complete logo should always remain visible.

Do not crop, partially hide or mask any part of the artwork.

---

# Do Not Redraw

Do not recreate the logo manually.

Avoid:

* Tracing
* Rebuilding
* Re-typing the wordmark
* Creating unofficial vector versions

Always use official files supplied by the LiVEiT® project.

---

# Do Not Alter Typography

The typography used within the official logo forms part of the protected visual identity.

Do not:

* Replace the typeface
* Adjust letter spacing
* Modify character shapes
* Rearrange text
* Create alternative wordmarks

---

# Do Not Use Low-Quality Images

Avoid:

* Pixelated graphics
* Blurred logos
* Compressed screenshots
* Low-resolution images

Use official SVG or high-quality artwork whenever possible.

---

# Do Not Ignore Clear Space

The required exclusion zone surrounding the logo should always be maintained.

Do not place:

* Text
* Images
* Buttons
* Icons
* Other logos

inside the required clear space.

---

# Do Not Use Busy Backgrounds

Avoid placing the logo on backgrounds that reduce visibility.

Examples include:

* Highly detailed photographs
* Strong patterns
* Low-contrast colours
* Visually complex graphics

If necessary, use an approved alternative logo that provides better contrast.

---

# Do Not Misrepresent the Brand

The LiVEiT® logo must not be used in any way that suggests:

* False endorsement
* Official partnership where none exists
* Ownership of the LiVEiT® trademark
* Authorisation that has not been granted

Use of the logo should always be accurate and truthful.

---

# Best Practice

When using the LiVEiT® logo:

* Use official artwork only.
* Preserve proportions.
* Maintain approved colours.
* Respect minimum sizing.
* Maintain clear space.
* Ensure good contrast.
* Follow the guidance provided throughout this Branding Guide.

Consistent application protects the integrity and recognition of the LiVEiT® brand.
